The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	 Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) may appoint Shahid Afridi as captain of their Test team as well. Pakistan are scheduled to play Test series against England and Australia in the United Kingdom after the Asia Cup in Sri Lanka. Wasim Bari, the PCB chief operating officer, said Afridi was one the candidates whom the Board will consider for the Test and oneday International captaincy after the World Twenty20.         
	Karachi: Pakistan leg-spinner Danish Kaneria is set to join his county side Essex next week despite speculation that he is one of the teams two players under investigation for spot fixing during a match last season. A British tabloid had named Kaneria as one of the players under the scanner although the Essex county and police have refused to divulge the names of the cricketers facing investigation.        
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) and Cricket South Africa (CSA) have reached an agreement to play a Test and ODI series in October this year in the UAE. A senior PCB official said the Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) for the series has almost been finalised and just a few things needed to be sorted out.        
	Karachi: Former Pakistan captain Younis Khan has told an appeals judge that he wants the countrys cricket Board to make public the evidence that led to them to impose an indefinite ban on him last month. Younis not only wants an early resolution to his appeal against the ban but also asked the appeals judge, Irfan Qadir, to direct the PCB to make public all evidence on the basis of which they banned him, his lawyer Ahmed Qayyum said on Friday.        
	New Delhi: Churchill Brothers will play Kuwaiti club Al Qadsia in their single-leg AFC Cup pre-quarterfinal match on May 12. The match will be played at Mohamed Al Hamed Stadium in Kuwait City, the home ground of Al Qadsia, who topped Group D. Under AFC rules, top teams of each of the eight groups play the single-leg round of 16 matches at home.         
	New Delhi: Asian champion Vikas Krishan (60kg) and Shiva Thapa (54kg) assured themselves of not just a medal but also a berth in the Youth Olympic Games after qualifying for the semis of the World Youth Boxing Championships in Baku, Azerbaijan Friday. While Shiva thrashed Russian Vadim Semin 13-3, Vikas blanked Irelands Michael OReilly 8-0.         
	New Delhi: Discus thrower Krishna Poonia produced a new personal best with a throw of 63.69m in the USA Olympic Training Centre Meet at Chula Vista in San Diego.         
	Chandigarh: Abhinav Bindra will participate in the European Cup International shooting competition at Hannovar, Germany.                                                                                                                                                      
